'''John Scott Inkster''' was a British [[Anesthesia|anesthesiologist]] born in 1924, one of the first paediatric anaesthetists. He graduated from the [[University of Aberdeen]] in 1945. Inkster's interest in anesthesia started during his time as a house physician at [[New End Hospital]]. John Inkster discovered [[Positive end-expiratory pressure]]<ref>http://www.apagbi.org.uk/about-us/membership/obituaries/dr-john-scott-inkster</ref>

John Inkster died on September 10, 2011.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Craft |first=Alan |year=2011 |title=John Scott Inkster |journal=[[The BMJ]] |volume=343 |doi=10.1136/bmj.d7517}}</ref>

