'''''Sex in Public''''' is an American [[reality television]] series that premiered on October 2, 2015, on [[TLC (TV network)|TLC]].<ref name="pressr">{{cite press release|title=Jill Dictrow Surprises People All Over the Country in New TLC Series ‘Sex in Public’|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/10/jill-dictorow-surprise-people-all-over-the-country-in-new-tlc-series-sex-in-public/|accessdate=December 29, 2015|date=September 10, 2015|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/09/29/sex-in-public-to-too-much-for-tv-tlc/|title=TLC’s ‘Sex in Public’ too much?|accessdate=December 29, 2015|date=September 30, 2015|first=Blanche|last=Johnson|publisher=[[Fox News Channel|Fox News]]}}</ref> The series is hosted by sex therapist Jill Dictrow who goes undercover in various places in order to approach people and help them dealing with their personal problems related to sex and dating.<ref name="pressr"/>

Despite its title, the series does not actually deal with situations related to [[public sex]] itself, but rather confronts people who are not comfortable openly discussing their sex lives.<ref name="boucott"/>

Due to its inappropriate content, the series was disapproved by the [[Parents Television Council]], which criticised the network's programming decisions and described the show as "a desperate move to attract attention."<ref name="boucott">{{cite web|work=[[Christian Today]]|accessdate=December 29, 2015|url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/desperate.tlc.slammed.for.replacing.19.kids.and.counting.with.sex.in.public/66258.htm|title='Desperate' TLC slammed for replacing '19 Kids and Counting' with 'Sex in Public'|date=October 2, 2015|first=Czarina|last=Ong}}</ref>

